        "body": "## Summary\n- add primary smoke-ci scorecard evidence links for six high-value already-covered behaviors\n- cover Control UI bootstrap, cron RPC/announce delivery, protected Prometheus scrape, media generation persistence, and thread placement\n- expand `smoke-ci` with deterministic channel delivery/thread categories, while keeping `release` as the full taxonomy selector via `includeAllCategories: true`\n- keep this as metadata/reporting coverage wiring; no release gate is added\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/coverage-report.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-packs.test.ts`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/qa-coverage-report.ts --json`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:extensions`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/qa-lab/src/coverage-report.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scorecard-taxonomy.ts qa/scenarios/ui/control-ui-qa-channel-image-roundtrip.yaml qa/scenarios/scheduling/cron-one-minute-ping.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/docker-prometheus-smoke.yaml qa/scenarios/media/image-generation-roundtrip.yaml qa/scenarios/channels/thread-follow-up.yaml`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Coverage impact\n- unknown taxonomy coverage IDs remain `0`\n- `smoke-ci`: `109 / 246` primary coverage refs fulfilled (`44.3%`), `73` missing-primary warnings, `0` missing-category warnings\n- `release`: all `281 / 281` taxonomy categories selected; `226 / 1948` primary coverage refs fulfilled (`11.6%`)\n- `release` has no category gaps and includes every `smoke-ci` category by construction\n- full release scorecard debt is visible: `1571` missing-primary warnings and `232` categories with no primary evidence yet\n\n## Review notes\n- kept `dangerous-tool-safeguards` unclaimed because the existing denial scenario does not attempt a dangerous tool\n- kept `image-and-pdf-input-routing` unclaimed because the existing media scenario only proves image attachment routing, not PDF routing\n- rebased on current `main`; the previous `c